Job Description
Main responsibilities:
Supervise and direct the work of all parties involved in fabrication yard activities for all projects, ensuring that all yard output is carried out on schedule and within budget, is based on sound engineering practice, design codes and standards and, is to the complete satisfaction of the Client.
Lead and motivate the team at the fabrication yard.
Foster effective working relations and ensure safety on the worksite.
Monitor and report on fabrication, construction and integration activities.
Monitor and report on mechanical completion and pre commissioning activities.
Ensure all fabrication yard activities are carried out in accordance with Project HSE, QA&QC requirements.
Identify and report on problem areas and oversee implementation of corrective actions.
Assist as required in the management, administration and training of personnel/systems/activities.
Demonstrate a personal commitment to HSE, QA&QC.
Requirements:
Degree Qualified in a relevant engineering discipline is essential.
Extensive Fabrication/Shipyard Construction Experience is essential.
10+ years proven track record of experience in an Oil&Gas projects environment.
Good working knowledge of project planning systems
Ability to identify QA/QC & HSE issues.
Ability to identify problems and propose solutions.
Interpersonal, communication, people management and leadership skills.
Conversant with standard computer software packages.
